  "texts": [
    "As the exploration of sensory perception continues, it is essential to understand the foundational mechanisms underlying both olfaction and gustation.",
    "These two senses not only enrich human experience but also interact in complex ways to shape overall flavor perception.",
    "This interplay informs various biological functions and emotional responses, necessitating a closer examination of the biological basis of each system.",
    "The olfactory system is a highly specialized sensory apparatus responsible for detecting and processing odorants, which are primarily volatile chemical compounds.",
    "This intricate system begins with the olfactory epithelium located in the nasal cavity, where approximately 400 distinct types of olfactory receptors are expressed (Firestein 2001)."
  ],
